sentences: Asad Ahmed (born 21 July 1971 in Karachi) is a Pakistani guitarist.
His family returned to Karachi in 1984.
Asad started his music career in 1987 with The Barbarians, which is regarded by many as Pakistan's first rock band.
They released their only album, the self-titled "The Barbarians" in 1989, which did not fare well in the then rock-repellant Pakistani music industry.
The Barbarians fell apart in 1990.
Asad did a gig with Salman Ahmad of Junoon at a party in 1991.

sentences: In a performance at Marriott Islamabad in November 1992, he met Haroon and Faakhir of Awaz and Rohail Hyatt of Vital Signs.

sentences: Awaz was formed in December 1992, by Haroon, Faakhir and Asad.
Awaz was the first band from Pakistan to appear on MTV on 20 April 1992 with the song Janeman.
In 1997, foreseeing a disintegrating Awaz, Asad established his own studio.
In 1999, Najam Shiraz returned to his solo career, vacating the vocalist's slot for newcomer Tanseer Daar.

In 2005, The band issued an internet only Unplugged album which had over 100,000 downloads.
Karavan released their fourth and final studio album, Saara Jahan in 2010.
The band broke up in 2012.
In 2017 he released Rebirth his first solo album which is also Pakistan's first all guitar instrumental album.
Will You was released as the third and final single on 4 July 2018.
Asad released his second solo album Severe Cuts [1] in July 2020.

sentences: Over the years, Asad has done extensive session work contributing his guitar work and compositions to albums by Vital Signs, Ali Zafar, Haroon, Sajjad Ali and Rahat Fateh Ali Khan to name a few.
On 14 August he also released a guitar rendition of the Pakistani National Anthem.
Rebirth the title track was released as the second single and video on 18 December.
The first single, "Dream of Right Now" [2]  was sent to Radio on 14 July.
